# Team data sync (always)

Published team pages must never show stale logos, covers, themes, or copy from browser cache or an old device session.

## Single source of truth

- **Production (Supabase configured):** `teams` row in Supabase is the only source of truth.
- **Never** merge `localStorage` preview drafts over server data when `usesCloudTeamStorage()` is true.
- Builder opens with `loadTeamForBuilder()` and clears `mts_team_preview_*` via `purgeStaleTeamPreview()`.

## Save contract

- Every save sends `team.updatedAt` (maps to `teams.updated_at`).
- `saveTeamContent` updates with `.eq("updated_at", lock)` — stale saves throw `STALE_TEAM_VERSION`.
- On stale save or newer server snapshot: reload from cloud (`loadTeamForBuilder`), do not keep local draft.
- When setting `logo_url`, also set `logo_path: null` so legacy storage paths cannot override.

## Logo resolution (`map-row.ts`)

Priority: `logo_url` → `page_settings.logoUrl` → hero settings → `logo_path` (only if no `logo_url`).

Never pass `publicLogoUrlFromPath(logo_path)` as fallback when `logo_url` is set.

## Public page cache

- `loadPublicTeamBySlug` uses `unstable_cache` with tag `public-team:{slug}`.
- After any coach save/publish: `revalidatePublicTeamPaths(slug)` (canonical `/{slug}` + legacy `/team/{slug}` redirect) and admin step-2.

## Sync policy (`lib/teams/sync-policy.ts`)

- Server wins when `isTeamVersionNewer(server.updatedAt, local.updatedAt)`.
- **While `dirty` and server is not newer, never replace local state** (mount sync, focus sync, `loadTeamForBuilder` on open).
- If not dirty, accept fresh server snapshot on focus/mount.

## Media uploads

- Files land in Supabase Storage `team-assets/{team_id}/{folder}/{file}` — RLS checks `team_members` for that `team_id`.
- Public URL saved on the team row: `teams.logo_url`, hero `blocks` JSON (`teamPhotoUrl`, `coverImageUrl`), etc.
- After every successful upload, `ImageUploadField` calls `flushSave()` → `saveTeamContent` with `updated_at` lock.
- Logo: `applyTeamLogoPatch` keeps `logo_url` and hero `teamPhotoUrl` in one state update.

## Backend layout (1000+ teams, one project)

| What | Where |
|------|--------|
| Team identity, blocks, theme | `public.teams` row (`id` = UUID, unique `slug`) |
| Logo URL (canonical) | `teams.logo_url` (+ hero block settings) |
| Coach membership | `public.team_members` (`team_id`, `user_id`) |
| Images/files | Storage bucket `team-assets` at `{team_id}/…` |
| Billing | `public.coach_subscriptions` per coach `user_id` |

Teams never share rows or storage prefixes — all queries filter by `team.id` / `team_id`.

## Do not

- Re-enable `mergeStoredPreview` or `saveTeamPreviewLocal` for cloud builds.
- Save full `TeamSpace` without `updatedAt` locking.
- Use `logo_path` when `logo_url` exists.
- Gate share bar or other critical UI behind nav state only (always show parent link + QR in toolbar).

## Tests

Run `npm test` — covers timestamp comparison, sync policy, logo fallback, and cloud preview storage.
